node.text: Hot pot is a dish that is best enjoyed as a group, and in Sichuan, it’s more customary to enjoy it at a restaurant (or to buy a prepackaged hot pot base) than to make it entirely from scratch. However, thanks to @meganjzhang and her Numbing Sichuan-Style Hot Pot recipe, you can learn to make it right from your home (dunking ingredients and dipping sauce options included!). Make it at the link in bio. 📸: @mj_kroeger

node.text: @emmalaperruque thinks your dirty martini Is due for an update, and that's where this week's #biglittlerecipes comes in. Her version is an almost-classic dirty martini, but she's using feta brine instead of olive brine. An extra trick? Squeeze a little feta into your olives! Get the recipe at the link in our bio. 📸@rockyluten
